article.headline: Radford routs Division II Catawba 88-52
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Javonte Green scored 17 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Radford to an 88-52 victory over Division II Catawba on Sunday. Cameron Jones hit a 3-pointer to cap a 13-0 run and give Radford an early 20-5 lead. Dominique Henderson's trey pulled the Indians within five points, 32-27 with 3:14 to play in the first half. The Highlanders closed the half with an 8-1 surge and led by double digits the rest of the way. Green shot 6 of 12 from the field. Davis scored 13 points, had four steals and dished out four assists for Radford (2-2), which finished with 11 steals and 17 assists. R.J. Price added 11 points for the Highlanders. Jameel Taylor scored 11 points on 5-of-5 shooting from the field, and was the only player in double figures for Catawba.
